I not long ago made a IIPA with 326 IBU...yes 326. How? 1.25 lbs hops, all
with AAs above 8% with most being 10% and above. Amarillo and Simcoe for FWH
and all the rest 30 minutes or less including 4 oz. in dry hop. It came out
1.084 OG and 1.018 FG. It's definately off balanced for most but I got what
I wanted...a beer you can almost smell through the bottle. The tase is
remeniscent of Bell's Hopslam and the taste pretty close to the same. I
always drink my IIPAs young as they tend to get too malty for me over 8
weeks in bottle. Then again people, even hopheads can only drink so much of
it. Me, I can't get too much hops but I will admit 1-22oz. bottle at a
sitting is enought to quench my taste for hops. And yes at 391 calories per
pint, it's a hearty meal to say the least. Some people like to mellow their
IPAs by letting them sit but IMHO it's defeating the whole idea of making an
IPA. Your choice...it's all about what you like :)

